Package: pheprobAoU
Type: Package
Title: Calculate PheProb (Phenotype Probabilities) Using All of Us EHR Data
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Alireza Ehteshami", "alireza.ehteshami@emory.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0001-9637-1695"))
Description: Implements the PheProb methodology (Sinnott et al., 2018) using binomial 
    mixture models for probabilistic phenotyping with electronic health record (EHR) 
    data from the All of Us Research Program. PheProb models disease-relevant billing 
    codes as a subset of total healthcare utilization, providing true phenotype 
    probabilities P(Y=1|S,C) where S is relevant code count and C is total healthcare 
    utilization. Supports multiple phenotype analysis, correlation assessment, and 
    comprehensive validation for biomedical research applications. See Sinnott et al. 
    (2018) <doi:10.1093/jamia/ocy056>.
